Environmental and agricultural samples including wastewater and apple were used to validate the MIP@Si-CDs sensor's recognition ability for determination of ACT. The standard addition method was used to measure ACT recoveries of samples (Table 2
                        ). The proposed prob. can be used to measure ACT in real samples, according to the results. The accuracy of the method in the analysis of ACT in the real samples of wastewater and apple samples was evaluated by comparison of the results from the method and standard method (HPLC) [29]. Triplicate measurements were used to calculate the ACT concentrations. Table 3
                         shows the statistical results. The comparison of the results shows no significant differences between these two analytical methods.
